Author: meatspoon#7860
Content: I have a noobish question that I hope you all will forgive me for...  I understand and appreciate and agree with the idea that whales might be driving this rally.  I know I understand close to nothing and can be wrong about anything (and I probably am!).  But I have been watching charts a lot for many, many months.  This recent BTC parabolic move over the last day/week has really nice consolidation patterns of lower/high higer/low within multiple time frames (4-hour, 1-hour, 15-minute).  This would lead me to believe that if the charts were being "painted" by whales that they would be using highly detailed small brushes on the 15 minute intervals to create their masterpiece.  Conclusion: seems unlikely this BTC surge is manufactured.  But my TA and crystal ball predictions both suck, so...
